theorem P1_closure_iff_closure_interior_closure_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (closure (A : Set X)) ↔
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hP1
    -- We already have `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))` from `P1`.
    -- The reverse inclusion holds in general.
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    ·
      -- Unfold `P1` for `closure A`.
      dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1
      exact hP1
    ·
      -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
      -- follows from monotonicity of `closure`.
      have h_subset :
          closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆
            closure (closure (A : Set X)) :=
        closure_interior_subset_closure (A := closure (A : Set X))
      simpa [closure_closure] using h_subset
  · intro hEq
    -- Use the equality to obtain the required inclusion for `P1`.
    dsimp [Topology.P1]
    intro x hx
    have : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
      simpa [hEq] using hx
    exact this
